    {
      "id": "CVE-2026-42512",
      "publishedDate": "2026-04-30T07:58:37.145Z",
      "lastModifiedDate": "2026-04-30T07:58:37.145Z",
      "description": "As dhclient is building an environment to pass to dhclient-script, it may need to resize the array of string pointers.  The code which expands the array incorrectly calculates its new size when requesting memory, resulting in a heap buffer overrun.\n\nA specially crafted packet can cause dhclient to overrun its buffer of environment entries.  This can result in a crash, but it may be possible to leverage this bug to achieve remote code execution.",
      "severity": "N/A",
      "references": [
        {
